Enable or disable lighting. **Lighting is enabled by default.**

{:.alert.alert-info}
When lighting is enabled you need to use the [material](/documentation/core/material.html)
function. The [color](/documentation/core/color.html) function should be used when 
lighting is disabled. Additionally, the various [geometry](/documentation/tags/geometry.html)
functions should be called with the optional `style="solid"` argument. See the [examples](#examples)
section below for examples of rendering with and without lighting.

### syntax

~~~ python
lighting(enable)
~~~

### parameters

enable | `True` or `False`


### examples

#### draw a solid sphere 


<%= vroom_example_image "core", "lighting", "draw-a-solid-sphere.png" %>


~~~ python
def display():
   lighting(True)
   material(1.0, 1.0, 1.0)
   sphere(3.0, style="solid")
~~~

#### draw a wireframe sphere


<%= vroom_example_image "core", "lighting", "draw-a-wireframe-sphere.png" %>


~~~ python
def display():
   lighting(False)
   color(1.0, 1.0, 1.0)
   sphere(3.0)
~~~
